ction repeatedly with the same raw response fixtures (case, whitespace, punctuation variants already resolved in fixture) and assert deterministic identical final label each run.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.9,"Integration":0.08,"System":0.01,"Agentic":0.01,"Workflow":0.0}},{"behavior_id":4,"description":"On repeated live API calls for the same document and taxonomy, the returned label remains consistent unless the provider response itself changes.","minimum_level":"Agentic","justification":"Behavior explicitly requires repeated live AI calls and depends on actual provider outputs over time. A stub would hide nondeterministic model-return effects and cannot validate the consistency condition against real provider variation. Rejected Workflow: this is repeated single-step classification calls, not a multi-step agent pipeline.","test_description":"Run N repeated real-provider classifications for the same input; log raw provider label and final module label each call; assert module label is stable whenever raw provider label is unchanged, and only changes when raw provider label changes.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.01,"Integration":0.04,"System":0.15,"Agentic":0.78,"Workflow":0.02}},{"behavior_id":5,"description":"Request construction enforces the configured token budget before dispatch (for example truncate/reject according to policy).","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"Real failure is often in wiring between token estimation/policy and dispatch gate (oversized payload still sent, or valid payload blocked). This is beyond a single pure function but does not require real network/OS or model output quality.","test_description":"Configure low budget, classify oversized and near-limit documents with a capturing stub client; assert policy action (truncate/reject) happens before dispatch and no over-budget request is sent.","plan_consistent":true,"plan